  <name>CHECK LINUX Security Tools</name>
  <summary>Comprehensive security audit and system optimization toolkit for Ubuntu Linux</summary>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      CHECK LINUX is a comprehensive toolkit designed to help system administrators, 
      DevOps professionals, and security enthusiasts secure and optimize Ubuntu Linux systems.
    </p>
    <p>Features include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Security Checklist: Comprehensive security audit with HTML/CSV reports</li>
      <li>System Updates verification: Check for available package updates</li>
      <li>Firewall analysis: UFW status and rules inspection</li>
      <li>Running Services review: Identify and review active services</li>
      <li>User Accounts audit: Find users with shell access and root-like accounts</li>
      <li>File Permissions check: Verify critical system files</li>
      <li>SSH Configuration analysis: Review SSH security settings</li>
      <li>Malware scanning: Integration with rkhunter (optional)</li>
      <li>Service Optimizer: Disable unnecessary services based on system type</li>
      <li>Sudo Permissions Checker: Audit sudo configurations</li>
      <li>Corporate Sudo Configurator: Create secure sudo policies</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The scripts are designed to be non-invasive and do not make automatic changes 
      to your system (except Service Optimizer in automatic mode when explicitly requested).
    </p>
    <p>
      Multi-language support available: English, Portuguese (Brazil), and Spanish.
    </p>
  </description>
  
